<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="PART-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT8" type="ext"/>PART VIII</designum></desig><title searchtype="PART-TITLE">LIMITATION PROCEEDINGS [rr 61&#x2013;64]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,765] r 61 Service on at least 1 respondent">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61" type="ext"/>[255,765]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Service on at least 1 respondent</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>61</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The applicant in a limitation proceeding must not apply:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>to have the proceeding set down for hearing; or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>for judgment in default of appearance;</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<p><text>unless at least 1 of the persons named as respondents in the initiating process has been served with initiating process.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An application referred to in 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.1.A" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">paragraph (1)(a)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 or 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.1.B" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">(b)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 must be supported by an affidavit setting out the name and, if known to the applicant, the address, of each other person who, to the knowledge of the applicant, has, or may have, a maritime claim against the applicant arising out of or connected with the matter in respect of which liability is to be limited.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255765-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,765.5]">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [255,765.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(CTH) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005X" refpt="CTH_ACT_1988-34" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Admiralty Act 1988</remotelink> 25, ss 3(1).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
<text>(CTH) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005X" refpt="CTH_REG_1988-269" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Admiralty Rules 1988</remotelink> Rules 61&#x2013;64.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255765-5" type="ext"/>[255,765.5] </edpnum></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>A limitation proceeding is a substantive application brought by a person seeking to limit his or her liability in accordance with international conventions on the ground that there was no &quot;actual fault or privity&quot; on his or her part in respect of the acts forming the basis of the underlying claim. See the Admiralty Act 1988 (Cth) 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADA88.S3.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">ss 3(1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 and 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADA88.S25" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">25</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
. 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R61" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Rules 61&#x2013;64</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 do not apply where a limitation of liability is raised solely by way of defence in an action. For an example of a limitation decree see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1938"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000100" spanref="cr000100-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CLR"/><ci:volume num="60"/><ci:page num="650"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000100" spanref="cr000100-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="678" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">James Patrick and Co Ltd v Union Steamship Co of New Zealand Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000100-001" status="unval">(1938) 60 CLR 650</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000100-002" status="unval">at 678&#x2013;80</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="6245" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>. Where a determination has been made and not set aside, the claimants must each establish their own cause of action against the plaintiff and can dispute each other's claims: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000101" spanref="cr000101-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="P"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1920"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="228"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000101" spanref="cr000101-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="233" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">The Disburser</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000101-001" status="unval">[1920] P 228</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000101-002" status="unval">at 233</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,770] r 62 Advertisement of determination">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62" type="ext"/>[255,770]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Advertisement of determination</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>62</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>In a limitation proceeding, if persons are identified as respondents in the initiating process by reference to their being members of a specified class of persons, the court must, after determining whether the liability of the applicant may be limited and the extent of that liability, make orders:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>specifying how the determination is to be advertised; and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>fixing a period, ending not less than 2 months after the latest day allowed for the advertisement of the determination, as the period within which a person who claims to have a maritime claim against the applicant in respect of which the applicant's liability has been determined:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.B.I"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.B.I" type="ext"/>(i)</lilabel>
<p><text>may prosecute that claim; or</text></p>
</li><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.B.II"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.B.II" type="ext"/>(ii)</lilabel>
<p><text>may apply under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">rule 64</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
</li></l></li>
</l><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37 and 1.38, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The advertisement of a determination must be in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F24" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 24</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The court need not make an order under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subrule (1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 if the court is satisfied that all members of the class of persons concerned have been served with initiating process.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R63"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,775] r 63 Effect of determination">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R63" type="ext"/>[255,775]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Effect of determination</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>63</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If a determination in a limitation proceeding has not been advertised under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">rule 62</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, the determination binds only persons identified as respondents in the initiating process who have been served with the initiating process.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[r 63  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.38, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,780] r 64 Proceedings to set aside determinations">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64" type="ext"/>[255,780]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Proceedings to set aside determinations</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>64</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If, in a limitation proceeding, the determination of the limit of the applicant's liability has been advertised in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">rule 62</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, the court may, on application in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F25" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 25</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 by a person who has not been served with initiating process, and on such terms and conditions as are just, vary or set aside the determination.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.38, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The application may not be made after the end of the period fixed under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R62.1.B" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">paragraph 62(1)(b)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The application and the affidavits in support must be served:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.3.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.3.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>on the applicant in the limitation proceeding; and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.3.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R64.3.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>on each respondent to that proceeding who entered an appearance in the proceeding;</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<p><text>not less than 7 days before the application is to be determined.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (3)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level></leg:levelbody></leg:level-vrnt></leg:level></leg:body></LEGDOC>